{
  "texts": [
    "Undetectable backdoorsGoldwasser et al. [42] discuss how a malicious actor can plant undetectable backdoors in machine learning models.",
    "These backdoors allow the actor to change the classification of any input with only a slight perturbation, which is undetectable without the appropriate \"backdoor key\".",
    "This poses a significant challenge to the monitoring of AI models.The backdoor consists of a pair of algorithms, one for training the model and another for activating the backdoor.",
    "The training algorithm, called Backdoor, returns a classifier and a backdoor key.",
    "The activation algorithm uses this key to slightly modify an input, causing the classifier to change its output."
  ]
}